{"title": "Three Years", "description": "Laptev, the rich but unattractive scion of a merchant, renounces his independent-minded, intelligent, devoted, but equally unattractive mistress Polina in order to marry the beautiful young gold-digger Yulia. Their life together quickly deteriorates into a loveless agony, Laptev seeking some sort of meaning in his life while Yulia whiles away her youth with the sparkling young Moscow social scene. The compelling question of the story is whether or not Laptev and Yulia can redeem something of lasting value from what seems to be a hopelessly empty relationship. Here Chekhov again explores the subtle dilemmas of modern conventional marriage and its effects, both positive and negative, on the hapless humans caught up in it. (summary by Expatriate)", "duration": 12442, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "147", "name": "Anton Chekhov"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/threeyears_1411_librivox/Three_Years_1411.jpg", "copyright_year": "1916", "genres": ["Literary Fiction"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Expatriate"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Expatriate"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "J. M. Smallheer"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "DaveC"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "Chapter 01", "readers": [8713], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/threeyears_1411_librivox/threeyears_01_chekhov_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1569}, {"section": 2, "title": "Chapter 02", "readers": [8713], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/threeyears_1411_librivox/threeyears_02_chekhov_64kb.mp3", "duration": 560}, {"section": 3, "title": "Chapter 03", "readers": [8713], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/threeyears_1411_librivox/threeyears_03_chekhov_64kb.mp3", "duration": 560}, {"section": 4, "title": "Chapter 04", "readers": [8713], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/threeyears_1411_librivox/threeyears_04_chekhov_64kb.mp3", "duration": 896}, {"section": 5, "title": "Chapter 05",